{
  "texts": [
    "Each job is tailored based on the user's preference (if any) and/or constraints of the computing resource.",
    "For example, if jobs are flexible in terms of duration and disk usage, they are generated to have a short execution time and produce small output files when processed on resources with limited time slots and local disk space.",
    "The task input is logically split into multiple subsets, and each job gets a subset to produce output.",
    "The collection of job outputs is the task output.",
    "Global ShareGlobal shares define the allocation of computing resources among various VO groups and/or user activities."
  ]
}